
[1]arena

   ARE'NA, n. [L. sand.]

   1. An open space of ground strewed with sand, on which the gladiators,
   in ancient Rome, exhibited shows of fighting for the amusement of
   spectators. Hence, a place for public exhibition.

   2. Among physicians, sand or gravel in the kidneys.
